CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 10, 1953, pg. 12 reads: "King And Queen - King and Queen of the Debutante Cotillion for 1953 were Roland Dent and Bernistine McClaney, who were crowned by the King and Queen of 1952. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: "Queen" Bernistine McClaney and "King" Roland Dent, walking through arch of debutantes and escorts arms, in Syria Mosque for 1953 Alpha Kappa Alpha cotillion
